cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper proposes a method for quantizing pre-trained full precision weights into ternary weights with minimal impact on accuracy, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of low-precision inference pipelines, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper explores the impact of different cluster sizes on performance and accuracy, which is related to computer architecture (cs.AR).
